WEBVTT

1
00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:51.480
How much?

2
00:01:51.560 --> 00:01:54.240
4:32. Unbelievable!

3
00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:55.880
Another record on your last day!

4
00:01:55.960 --> 00:01:57.080
It's a souvenir...

5
00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:00.680
You can frame that watch now.
you won't need it anymore...

6
00:02:00.715 --> 00:02:05.560
A speech! A speech!

7
00:02:12.441 --> 00:02:13.561
Where is my little Daniel?

8
00:02:25.601 --> 00:02:29.601
Like you all know
Daniel resigned last night.

9
00:02:30.601 --> 00:02:33.601
He quits the 2 wheelers
for the 4 wheelers

10
00:02:34.641 --> 00:02:39.361
He's the opposite of human evolution
that starts on all fours...

11
00:02:39.441 --> 00:02:41.361
...and nobly finishes on two wheels!

12
00:02:41.481 --> 00:02:44.601
I want him to know
that he was the best of us all...

13
00:02:44.681 --> 00:02:47.881
...and most of all.
most of all. a very good friend.

14
00:02:48.641 --> 00:02:50.281
We are all gonna miss you. you know!

15
00:03:05.642 --> 00:03:08.642
Err... sorry Lily. was that a kiss?
Or did your lips just slip?

16
00:03:09.642 --> 00:03:12.642
It's not that it bothered me
but I don't know what to think...

17
00:03:18.482 --> 00:03:19.482
Is it clearer now?

18
00:03:22.162 --> 00:03:24.162
Yep! Yep!

19
00:03:24.682 --> 00:03:27.642
Because if they slipped again.
your aim really sucks!

20
00:03:30.683 --> 00:03:32.643
And now to celebrate
Daniel's departure...

21
00:03:33.683 --> 00:03:35.683
...I announce the big parade!

22
00:03:36.683 --> 00:03:40.283
Open your eyes wide. Lily.
because you won't see this often.

23
00:03:40.523 --> 00:03:41.403
How many are they?

24
00:03:41.483 --> 00:03:42.483
Oh. a lot!

25
00:03:56.883 --> 00:03:58.283
They're the best!

26
00:04:05.723 --> 00:04:06.883
Go for it!

27
00:04:14.564 --> 00:04:15.524
Holy shit!

28
00:04:37.004 --> 00:04:37.884
You rule!

29
00:04:48.484 --> 00:04:49.684
So we're having a little party?

30
00:04:49.764 --> 00:04:51.284
Are they from the pizzeria too?

31
00:04:51.685 --> 00:04:52.405
Not exactly. no.

32
00:04:52.485 --> 00:04:55.645
Looks like you'll have to show us your papers.

33
00:04:55.885 --> 00:04:59.725
Sorry we left them inside
but if you want we can go get them now.

34
00:04:59.885 --> 00:05:01.205
Ok. but make it fast.

35
00:05:01.285 --> 00:05:04.085
No problem. thanks.

36
00:05:15.805 --> 00:05:18.085
It must have been at least 5 minutes now.

37
00:05:35.846 --> 00:05:37.286
Watch it. there could be some oil.

38
00:05:37.686 --> 00:05:38.806
Oil?

39
00:05:39.846 --> 00:05:43.286
Yeah. it's my flat
but it's also kind of my garage...

40
00:05:45.846 --> 00:05:48.286
It's... it's not much...

41
00:05:50.846 --> 00:05:51.806
Humm. it's... special.

42
00:05:52.846 --> 00:05:53.766
Daniel?

43
00:05:53.886 --> 00:05:54.566
Yes?

44
00:05:54.686 --> 00:05:56.646
We've known each other for 2 years now.

45
00:05:57.686 --> 00:05:59.806
Why did you wait for your last day?

46
00:05:59.926 --> 00:06:02.686
I'm a bit slow. I take forever to decide.

47
00:06:02.886 --> 00:06:03.846
And what made you decide?

48
00:06:07.086 --> 00:06:08.086
Your cleavage.

49
00:06:09.086 --> 00:06:10.086
It's nice. hey?

50
00:06:10.887 --> 00:06:11.847
The dress is brand new.

51
00:06:12.887 --> 00:06:15.487
Ok then... we'll try not to damage it.

52
00:06:16.887 --> 00:06:19.607
You're sure it's a good idea
after years of friendship?

53
00:06:19.887 --> 00:06:21.927
We prepared the terrain well.
now it's time to build on it.

54
00:06:22.687 --> 00:06:24.487
Maybe we should wait a little more?

55
00:06:24.527 --> 00:06:25.287
No. if I wait any longer...

56
00:06:25.327 --> 00:06:28.807
...I'm worried that you would take it badly
and I don't want to be impolite.

57
00:06:34.567 --> 00:06:35.687
Oh. no!

58
00:06:35.767 --> 00:06:36.087
What?

59
00:06:36.887 --> 00:06:37.487
It's 6 o'clock.

60
00:06:37.567 --> 00:06:38.887
Who cares. it's Saturday!

61
00:06:38.967 --> 00:06:40.487
Yes. but I have to go to a meeting for my job.

62
00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:41.487
What?

63
00:06:41.927 --> 00:06:44.607
You just quit.
did you already find a new job during the night?

64
00:06:44.727 --> 00:06:46.847
Of course not. it's a meeting for my future job...

65
00:06:46.967 --> 00:06:49.687
...a meeting I had to arrange
months in advance.

66
00:06:49.927 --> 00:06:52.887
But you've been waiting for our meeting
for months...

67
00:06:53.688 --> 00:06:57.088
Yes. months plus one hour.
And that's one hour maximum!

68
00:07:09.928 --> 00:07:12.288
Hey you. just take a number over there.

69
00:07:23.288 --> 00:07:26.888
And don't forget your pictures next time.
77!

70
00:07:27.008 --> 00:07:30.488
247. Wonder if she'll even get there today...

71
00:07:35.689 --> 00:07:36.889
How long have you been a driver?

72
00:07:36.969 --> 00:07:38.689
25 years yesterday.

73
00:07:38.969 --> 00:07:40.929
I retired this morning.

74
00:07:41.049 --> 00:07:45.489
It's the first morning in 25 years
that I can read the news.

75
00:07:46.489 --> 00:07:47.689
Ah I see...

76
00:07:56.289 --> 00:07:58.689
Wake up there. number 247!

77
00:08:00.089 --> 00:08:01.014
He's right here!

78
00:08:01.049 --> 00:08:06.289
Your ticket. 2 pictures...
sign here... and here.

79
00:08:08.009 --> 00:08:11.489
So. that's your professional licence.
driving certificate....

80
00:08:13.010 --> 00:08:19.490
...new car permit.
notepad. license plate and the sign.

81
00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:24.890
That's it?

82
00:08:24.970 --> 00:08:26.090
Why. yes.

83
00:08:28.690 --> 00:08:30.290
After 6 years?

84
00:08:30.370 --> 00:08:31.890
You want the national anthem?

85
00:08:32.010 --> 00:08:34.810
Well a little smile would have been nice.

86
00:08:38.010 --> 00:08:39.290
248!

87
00:08:41.010 --> 00:08:41.850
Lily!

88
00:08:46.010 --> 00:08:48.010
I went to buy some croissants myself...

89
00:08:48.090 --> 00:08:50.490
...and out of despair. I married the baker.

90
00:08:50.891 --> 00:08:53.091
Farewell... and see you later.

91
00:09:07.891 --> 00:09:10.691
Well congratulations. Mr. Daniel!

92
00:09:10.771 --> 00:09:12.011
Bah. you're welcome.

93
00:09:12.091 --> 00:09:13.691
Oh but please. I insist!

94
00:09:13.771 --> 00:09:14.891
Well. ok then...

95
00:09:54.892 --> 00:09:55.892
Hi. Daniel!

96
00:09:55.972 --> 00:09:56.492
Hey. Paulo!

97
00:09:57.092 --> 00:09:58.412
You're doing in tourism now?

98
00:09:58.532 --> 00:09:58.892
Yeah...

99
00:09:59.092 --> 00:10:01.892
The party and the parade were great.
we smoked pot like hell!

100
00:10:02.092 --> 00:10:04.292
Yep. it was great.
But listen Paulo. I'm worried...

101
00:10:04.372 --> 00:10:05.292
Why. what's wrong?

102
00:10:05.332 --> 00:10:08.092
Your bike makes a weird noise.
Is it working. at least?

103
00:10:08.172 --> 00:10:10.092
You kidding me?
I fill it with vitriol!

104
00:10:10.173 --> 00:10:14.493
I had two cops on my ass earlier.
you should've seen how they bit the dust!

105
00:10:14.893 --> 00:10:18.093
Watch this: 2 cops at the red light up the avenue.

106
00:10:19.133 --> 00:10:23.053
Lights change and I'm away and gone
before they even shifted gear!

107
00:10:23.213 --> 00:10:27.093
They were so absolutely pissed!

108
00:10:27.213 --> 00:10:33.093
I slammed the hammer down in the tunnel.
and those cops were crying for their mummy!

109
00:10:33.213 --> 00:10:36.133
I'm telling you. they won't forget
Paulo anytime soon!

110
00:10:36.213 --> 00:10:40.093
Paulo... I can roger that. Paulo.
They did NOT forget you.

111
00:10:43.173 --> 00:10:46.493
Hey girlies!
Still wearing that moustache?

112
00:10:55.174 --> 00:10:56.294
Go. Paulo!

113
00:10:59.174 --> 00:11:02.134
Hey girls! Going to the beach?
I drive for free today!

114
00:11:02.254 --> 00:11:04.494
It would be my pleasure!
Come on!

115
00:11:04.694 --> 00:11:09.094
Hey. hey. are you a "Tijuana taxi"
or a nice taxi?

116
00:11:09.294 --> 00:11:11.694
I'm the super-nice kind!

117
00:11:12.094 --> 00:11:17.294
I open the door to ladies. don't make you
car sick. shut up unless asked...

118
00:11:17.494 --> 00:11:19.894
...and I even carry bags if you ask nicely.

119
00:11:19.974 --> 00:11:22.694
Thank you. that's perfect. perfect!

120
00:11:29.094 --> 00:11:30.494
So where are we going. miss?

121
00:11:31.095 --> 00:11:35.295
You see the pink house over there.
with that big door?

122
00:11:35.895 --> 00:11:36.695
Well yeah. I see it.

123
00:11:36.775 --> 00:11:39.095
Ok. this is where we are going.

124
00:11:44.215 --> 00:11:46.495
I bet you have a favorite
route to get there?

125
00:11:48.215 --> 00:11:50.895
Just put all that stuff in the kitchen.
I'll store it away later.

126
00:11:51.295 --> 00:11:53.295
Now there's enough food for the whole week!

127
00:11:53.335 --> 00:11:56.175
You're wrong. my son is coming for lunch.

128
00:11:56.295 --> 00:11:57.735
What. he eats all that in one meal?

129
00:11:57.815 --> 00:11:59.855
Of course not. Sunday I'm preparing...

130
00:11:59.895 --> 00:12:01.495
...all his meals for the week...

131
00:12:01.535 --> 00:12:04.215
... his flat is so small.
there's not even a kitchen.

132
00:12:04.295 --> 00:12:07.215
Besides. the poor kid can't even cook an egg.

133
00:12:07.295 --> 00:12:10.695
Look.
That's him on the picture. there...

134
00:12:11.256 --> 00:12:15.696
He's a real computer geek.
He works for IBM.

135
00:12:15.776 --> 00:12:17.296
To each his own...

136
00:12:17.376 --> 00:12:19.296
Right... what's your thing?

137
00:12:19.336 --> 00:12:22.896
Driving.
but I doubt you had time to see that.

138
00:12:23.096 --> 00:12:27.216
Funny. my son is having his driving exam today
for the 8th time!

139
00:12:27.336 --> 00:12:31.296
8 times...! Well. 8 is my lucky number.
I'm sure it'll help him.

140
00:12:34.256 --> 00:12:36.896
At the end of the street.
we are going to take the first to the...

141
00:12:37.256 --> 00:12:38.496
...to the...to the...the?

142
00:12:38.896 --> 00:12:41.896
...to the left. Mr. Carbedec.

143
00:12:43.496 --> 00:12:45.296
Turn left. Mr. Carbedec. LEFT!

144
00:12:45.536 --> 00:12:49.696
Turn left. we're gonna crash!
Are you retarded or what? LEFT!

145
00:12:51.297 --> 00:12:56.097
Holy shit! I don't believe this!
I've never seen such an idiot in 10 years!

146
00:12:56.297 --> 00:12:58.257
Can't you tell your right from your left?

147
00:13:00.297 --> 00:13:01.297
Well you should have told me earlier!

148
00:13:01.377 --> 00:13:03.257
You need to get a fax to turn left?

149
00:13:03.377 --> 00:13:07.497
Left is just left!
Shit. just turn the wheel and step on the pedal!

150
00:13:08.297 --> 00:13:09.377
Well to each his job.

151
00:13:09.417 --> 00:13:10.497
Oh yeah? What's yours?

152
00:13:11.297 --> 00:13:13.257
I wonder where they would hire an ape like that?

153
00:13:13.377 --> 00:13:15.497
Where do you work?
In a circus. a zoo. the CIA or what?

154
00:13:15.577 --> 00:13:16.897
A mix of all 3...

155
00:13:20.297 --> 00:13:22.297
You should have told me earlier. sir...

156
00:13:22.377 --> 00:13:23.697
I should have sent you a fax?

157
00:13:24.337 --> 00:13:25.297
Excuse me.

158
00:13:26.337 --> 00:13:28.297
Can I offer you something Mr. Inspector?

159
00:13:30.178 --> 00:13:31.138
Oh thank you. it looks great!

160
00:13:31.298 --> 00:13:35.698
No. I thank you! You were so nice.
I'll keep your card preciously!

161
00:13:36.338 --> 00:13:40.298
Would you mind if I eat it in my car?
Because I think I should go back to work...

162
00:13:40.418 --> 00:13:43.098
Of course not! Go on. back to work!

163
00:13:50.338 --> 00:13:51.498
Can you save my life?

164
00:13:51.578 --> 00:13:53.498
Well basically... no.

165
00:13:55.338 --> 00:13:58.098
Well... it depends. what are your symptoms?

166
00:13:58.178 --> 00:14:01.338
I have to catch a flight in 25 minutes.
If I miss it. I'm a dead man.

167
00:14:01.418 --> 00:14:03.498
But if I make it. you're a rich man!

168
00:14:06.178 --> 00:14:07.178
Humm... Mister is lucky.

169
00:14:08.218 --> 00:14:09.178
I'm no physician...

170
00:14:10.379 --> 00:14:13.699
...but I like emergencies!
Can you buckle up. please?

171
00:14:46.419 --> 00:14:48.219
Maybe we should get going now!

172
00:14:53.500 --> 00:14:54.900
And here we go!

173
00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:29.180
White taxi at incredible speed!

174
00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:31.540
- He knocked my radar over!
- What's his number?

175
00:15:31.621 --> 00:15:33.181
I didn't get it. it was too fast!

176
00:15:33.221 --> 00:15:36.181
Hey man. open your eyes! That's your job!

177
00:15:43.461 --> 00:15:44.901
Do you think we'll make it?

178
00:15:45.701 --> 00:15:49.101
Because if not
maybe we should just take our time...

179
00:15:49.461 --> 00:15:53.701
We'll be fine. Going slow now.
but we'll gain some speed on the highway.

180
00:16:14.502 --> 00:16:16.462
Don't take all those risks just for me. sir..

181
00:16:17.502 --> 00:16:19.462
I don't want you to lose your licence!

182
00:16:19.582 --> 00:16:21.902
Don't worry.
I ain't got one anyway.

183
00:16:24.302 --> 00:16:25.702
Ah... that's... great.

184
00:16:40.502 --> 00:16:42.502
14 minutes and 30 seconds!

185
00:16:42.582 --> 00:16:46.342
Enough time to read the paper and get a coffee.
Have a safe trip. sir!

186
00:16:47.542 --> 00:16:48.342
Thank you...

187
00:17:04.383 --> 00:17:05.343
I don't get it.

188
00:17:09.303 --> 00:17:10.503
On a computer I'm invincible!

189
00:17:10.623 --> 00:17:13.703
Best in the championship. lap record in Monaco.
8 pole positions.

190
00:17:14.503 --> 00:17:16.503
But as soon as I'm on the streets. I crash.

191
00:17:17.423 --> 00:17:20.503
So? We're gonna drink it now. eh?

192
00:17:20.543 --> 00:17:21.103
No. not that soon.

193
00:17:21.583 --> 00:17:27.543
Oh c'mon Emilien. that can't be!
I know they say champagne gets better with time...

194
00:17:27.623 --> 00:17:31.383
... but by now it's gotta be almost vinegar!
What happened this time?

195
00:17:31.584 --> 00:17:34.104
Hit a butcher's...
a change from newspaper stands!

196
00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:34.904
You know what?

197
00:17:36.424 --> 00:17:39.304
You should put a computer mouse
instead of a wheel in your car.

198
00:17:39.504 --> 00:17:43.424
Seriously. I swear some disabled guys do that!
What...?

199
00:17:43.504 --> 00:17:44.304
Oh come on...

200
00:17:44.504 --> 00:17:49.704
Don't throw me that look there. oh la la...
What'd I say?

201
00:17:51.584 --> 00:17:53.544
Emilien. we just got a new record.

202
00:17:54.584 --> 00:17:56.824
A taxi. near the harbour.
Guess how fast?

203
00:17:56.904 --> 00:17:57.904
140 km/h?

204
00:17:57.944 --> 00:17:59.024
In first gear. yes...

205
00:17:59.104 --> 00:18:01.904
Then he switched to second gear:
217 km/h!

206
00:18:02.024 --> 00:18:03.304
Did you get it?

207
00:18:03.344 --> 00:18:04.904
Of course. they called in for air support...

208
00:18:04.984 --> 00:18:05.904
Imagine. at that speed!

209
00:18:06.624 --> 00:18:09.584
Hey. did you hear that new joke?
Listen. it's really funny.

210
00:18:09.665 --> 00:18:12.585
What is the difference between a comb and an egg?

211
00:18:16.625 --> 00:18:20.265
Err. I see... I'll just come back later. ok?

212
00:18:20.305 --> 00:18:20.905
Yeah that's right!

213
00:18:20.985 --> 00:18:24.105
Much MUCH later. for example after nightfall!

214
00:18:24.625 --> 00:18:26.905
AND NEXT TIME. KNOCK BEFORE YOU ENTER!

215
00:18:30.705 --> 00:18:31.425
Petra...

216
00:18:33.465 --> 00:18:35.625
I didn't say that for you...
you are always welcome!

217
00:18:35.705 --> 00:18:39.625
Thanks. my little Emilien.
Heard there was a problem with your license?

218
00:18:39.705 --> 00:18:41.625
The news get around fast...

219
00:18:42.505 --> 00:18:47.305
Talking about news. I got some!
Everybody's at the Chief's meeting. except... you!

220
00:18:47.665 --> 00:18:48.905
Ah no... we weren't advised!

221
00:18:48.985 --> 00:18:51.385
You know. you just have to push that button...

222
00:18:51.506 --> 00:18:54.106
... see there. it says "power"...!

223
00:18:54.506 --> 00:18:57.666
...YOU GET THAT? I SAID IMMEDIATELY.
ARE YOU DEAF EMILIEN?

224
00:18:57.786 --> 00:18:59.106
Not anymore. chief!

225
00:18:59.666 --> 00:19:03.386
So guys. after hitting banks in the Netherlands.
Italy and Belgium...

226
00:19:03.506 --> 00:19:05.386
...the "Mercedes Gang" just arrived in France.

227
00:19:05.506 --> 00:19:09.706
I will NOT allow the Tutons
to conquer our territory again!

228
00:19:10.666 --> 00:19:13.626
My grandpa died at their hands.
so this is a personnal matter.

229
00:19:13.746 --> 00:19:17.666
So the Paris-Bonn link and German-French
friendship... Kiss my ass!

230
00:19:17.746 --> 00:19:20.666
Got that?
Now I don't mean that against you. Petra.

231
00:19:20.906 --> 00:19:23.106
You're German... right.
but you're also a cop so that's ok.

232
00:19:23.706 --> 00:19:26.666
And they even got the chutzpah to inform
the cities they'll hit in advance!

233
00:19:26.746 --> 00:19:27.666
That's outrageous!

234
00:19:27.746 --> 00:19:30.666
It will be a bank in Marseille within 3 days!

235
00:19:30.747 --> 00:19:33.707
RED ALEEERT!
24 hours a day!

236
00:19:34.707 --> 00:19:37.307
SWATs are supporting us.
we get one driver per team.

237
00:19:37.627 --> 00:19:42.427
As soon as the Tutons leave the bank.
our teams will follow them...

238
00:19:42.547 --> 00:19:45.907
...they'll stick to their tail.
acting like a venom...

239
00:19:46.707 --> 00:19:48.667
That's why this operation will be called...

240
00:19:50.107 --> 00:19:50.747
...Cobra!

241
00:19:52.707 --> 00:19:54.467
Petra. can you please assemble the teams?

242
00:19:54.707 --> 00:19:59.707
3 per car.
One SWAT driver. one coordinator and a sniper.

243
00:19:59.787 --> 00:20:03.467
Each team takes a codename and a position
as shown on the map behind you.

244
00:20:03.547 --> 00:20:05.707
Team members are listed next to the map.

245
00:20:05.787 --> 00:20:08.307
You have 50 minutes to get in position.

246
00:20:08.747 --> 00:20:12.107
Petra? Sorry. it's about that dinner...

247
00:20:12.748 --> 00:20:14.708
...this week would be nice. because...

248
00:20:14.828 --> 00:20:18.508
...see. the software that I developed...

249
00:20:19.508 --> 00:20:22.708
...we shouldn't wait too long.
somebody could steal the idea. you see?

250
00:20:22.828 --> 00:20:26.108
No. What can't wait. you or the software?

251
00:20:26.148 --> 00:20:26.708
Well it's me...

252
00:20:26.828 --> 00:20:29.708
I mean. it... the software... the computer...ahhh!

253
00:20:29.908 --> 00:20:33.708
You see. it's complicated!
That's why I thought that...

254
00:20:34.748 --> 00:20:35.748
...a dinner...

255
00:20:37.748 --> 00:20:41.748
As soon as we got the Germans.
I'm going to take care of you...

256
00:20:41.828 --> 00:20:43.108
...I mean. of the software!

257
00:20:43.148 --> 00:20:44.748
Oh. ok. that's great!

258
00:20:44.828 --> 00:20:46.708
By the way. what's your team?

259
00:20:46.748 --> 00:20:47.748
I'm with the Cobra. but...

260
00:20:47.828 --> 00:20:50.508
... you're lucky. I put you in the best team.

261
00:21:19.789 --> 00:21:22.509
Looks like we're out of coffee...

262
00:21:26.829 --> 00:21:29.509
See that steering wheel?
Great. huh? It's my own...

263
00:21:29.710 --> 00:21:31.710
...got it from Alain Prost in person.

264
00:21:32.830 --> 00:21:35.230
...has a new grip. special "Indy 500".

265
00:21:35.310 --> 00:21:38.510
Even with a ton of sand. you're driving fine.

266
00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:41.510
Oh yeah?
Too bad we're not at the beach then.

267
00:21:42.110 --> 00:21:44.310
Hey. no smoking. it irritates my eyes.

268
00:21:44.390 --> 00:21:46.110
No coffee. no smoking...

269
00:21:46.150 --> 00:21:47.310
And no chicks. either!

270
00:21:50.830 --> 00:21:54.510
Boa calls Grass Snake.
I repeat: Boa calls Grass Snake.

271
00:21:54.550 --> 00:21:55.310
Grass Snake here. what's up?

272
00:21:55.350 --> 00:21:57.590
Hey. it's Alain. Everything ok?

273
00:21:57.670 --> 00:21:59.710
Just great.
We're already swapping addresses.

274
00:21:59.790 --> 00:22:00.310
And you?

275
00:22:00.390 --> 00:22:02.710
We're about to get pissed at.
but else we're just fine...

276
00:22:03.870 --> 00:22:07.830
Hey Rachid. see the black car behind us?
Let's take it!

277
00:22:07.910 --> 00:22:11.110
Fuck. Marco. you nuts?
Wanna steal a car in broad daylight?

278
00:22:11.311 --> 00:22:14.111
Why not? Watch this...

279
00:22:14.511 --> 00:22:16.591
Fuck. Marco. stop it!
It's full of cops around here!

280
00:22:16.711 --> 00:22:19.711
That's not our neighborhood.
let's stick to what we know!

281
00:22:19.871 --> 00:22:23.831
Cool down. man. no problem!
All the cops are at the airport!

282
00:22:23.951 --> 00:22:27.311
There isn't a cop for miles around!
Now watch this...

283
00:22:27.871 --> 00:22:28.831
What. you're really gonna do it?

284
00:22:28.911 --> 00:22:31.111
Relax!
I told you. all the cops are at the airport!

285
00:22:31.871 --> 00:22:35.511
I've seen it on TV. there's Clinton
and his chick meeting the Russians! Watch me!

286
00:22:35.871 --> 00:22:39.911
Hey there. cops! Marco's here!
Now watch him screw you. fuck you. smoke you...!

287
00:22:39.951 --> 00:22:41.231
Let's grab him now!

288
00:22:41.311 --> 00:22:43.311
No. no. let him take that trash car...

289
00:22:43.511 --> 00:22:44.871
We need all the space we can get.

290
00:22:46.911 --> 00:22:48.631
Listen. I gotta go take a piss.

291
00:22:48.751 --> 00:22:50.711
Nobody gets out of the car. That's the orders.

292
00:22:53.912 --> 00:22:56.512
See? I told you. they're all at the airport!

293
00:22:58.912 --> 00:23:01.712
Smile guys. you're on candid camera...!

294
00:23:02.432 --> 00:23:04.672
Listen. if that Mercedes doesn't get here
within one minute...

295
00:23:04.712 --> 00:23:07.512
...I'm getting a coffee. smoke. and WC!
Got that?

296
00:23:07.712 --> 00:23:09.512
We'll do all that later. pal.

297
00:23:15.712 --> 00:23:18.712
To all snakes:
no venom until the mouse gets out of the hole.

298
00:23:18.912 --> 00:23:21.512
I repeat. no venom before the exit.

299
00:23:21.632 --> 00:23:22.112
Inspector?

300
00:23:22.192 --> 00:23:24.672
Oh no Petra. I was just getting into it!

301
00:23:24.752 --> 00:23:26.312
I know but... it's the minister.

302
00:23:27.952 --> 00:23:30.312
My respects. sir. Aren't you at the airport?

303
00:23:30.393 --> 00:23:32.193
We just finished. Tell me. Gilbert...

304
00:23:32.313 --> 00:23:34.313
...so what about that Mercedes gang?

305
00:23:34.393 --> 00:23:38.913
Well. we localised them
and we're just about to take action.

306
00:23:39.033 --> 00:23:39.713
Good. good. but...

307
00:23:39.793 --> 00:23:41.913
... I just talked with my German colleague...

308
00:23:41.993 --> 00:23:43.313
Hold it right there. sir.

309
00:23:43.393 --> 00:23:45.913
Those nazis won't have time to visit Marseille.

310
00:23:46.033 --> 00:23:48.313
By tomorrow I'm sending them
back to their country...

311
00:23:48.393 --> 00:23:49.273
...as special cargo...

312
00:23:49.313 --> 00:23:53.433
Listen. I don't want this to end
as a German-French shootdown.

313
00:23:53.513 --> 00:23:54.913
The war is over my dear Gilbert!

314
00:23:54.993 --> 00:23:56.513
Ah but absolutely sir...

315
00:23:56.553 --> 00:24:01.713
...I understand perfectly. they are just
common criminals and will be treated as such.

316
00:24:01.793 --> 00:24:04.713
Well then stop calling them nazis.
for example...

317
00:24:04.993 --> 00:24:06.113
What. I called them nazis?

318
00:24:06.193 --> 00:24:06.913
Well yes.

319
00:24:07.993 --> 00:24:08.913
I called them nazis?

320
00:24:08.954 --> 00:24:09.314
Yes...

321
00:24:10.314 --> 00:24:12.114
My tongue must've slipped because...

322
00:24:12.234 --> 00:24:13.394
So I can count on you then?

323
00:24:13.474 --> 00:24:15.714
Of course you can. remember the gooks...

324
00:24:16.114 --> 00:24:20.514
...err I mean the Asians.
Everything went smoothly.

325
00:24:20.594 --> 00:24:23.914
Almost no casualties...
...at least. not on our side...

326
00:24:25.994 --> 00:24:30.434
Hello? Hello?
He just hung up!

327
00:24:43.834 --> 00:24:44.834
You see. it's easy!

328
00:24:49.795 --> 00:24:51.315
Where are those cables...

329
00:24:51.355 --> 00:24:52.435
Shit. Marco! Hurry!

330
00:24:52.515 --> 00:24:54.915
You're gonna move that car. asshole
or do you need the keys?

331
00:24:59.715 --> 00:25:03.715
We are the "Grass Snakes".
meaning that we're small and COOL.

332
00:25:03.915 --> 00:25:07.115
So we're gonna take this rather
"COOL" than venimous. ok?

333
00:25:12.515 --> 00:25:15.795
To all the snakes. don't miss the worms.
we want them alive...

334
00:25:15.875 --> 00:25:16.835
...at least for one hour...

335
00:25:22.915 --> 00:25:25.515
I'd better let you guys
handle that alone then. ok?

336
00:25:27.515 --> 00:25:29.915
Plus...
...I really gotta take a leak. now!

337
00:25:37.516 --> 00:25:38.716
GO!

338
00:25:42.116 --> 00:25:43.516
What is going on?

339
00:25:43.596 --> 00:25:45.036
Something smells fishy. sir!

340
00:25:48.116 --> 00:25:49.036
Don't move. sir!

341
00:25:58.116 --> 00:25:58.876
Holy shit!

342
00:26:00.116 --> 00:26:03.116
We've been ambushed. send us backup!

343
00:26:06.116 --> 00:26:07.916
I identified the car...

344
00:26:10.317 --> 00:26:13.717
Please take note. I identified the second car!

345
00:26:13.997 --> 00:26:15.437
There are 4 well trained men aboard.

346
00:26:15.517 --> 00:26:17.117
Backup is on the way. sir!

347
00:26:27.997 --> 00:26:29.077
Oh shit. oh shit!

348
00:26:55.198 --> 00:26:57.318
Sir... I think we are shooting at cops. sir!

349
00:27:00.278 --> 00:27:01.238
Looks like they're yielding. no?

350
00:27:03.278 --> 00:27:09.958
Hello...? Grass Snake here...
We had a small problem with the door...

351
00:27:11.198 --> 00:27:13.318
Hello sir.
Don't worry. you'll be out of here in 5 min.

352
00:27:15.198 --> 00:27:16.518
Err... no problem. no problem...!

353
00:27:16.598 --> 00:27:17.158
Thank you sir.

354
00:27:20.038 --> 00:27:20.998
That's it. they are yielding now!

355
00:27:24.198 --> 00:27:27.198
Hey that's funny... he looks just a bit like...

356
00:27:27.278 --> 00:27:32.918
...like the minister... huh? Huh?

357
00:27:34.239 --> 00:27:36.039
Oh sweetie. you didn't eat anything!

358
00:27:36.079 --> 00:27:38.159
I'm not really hungry today.

359
00:27:38.519 --> 00:27:40.119
Mom. stop it!

360
00:27:40.199 --> 00:27:42.519
Stop worrying about your licence.

361
00:27:43.239 --> 00:27:46.119
Remember your father. he never got it.

362
00:27:46.159 --> 00:27:47.159
What do you mean?

363
00:27:47.319 --> 00:27:49.319
I remember him driving when I was young!

364
00:27:49.359 --> 00:27:50.599
That's true.

365
00:27:50.679 --> 00:27:54.119
He tried the test 20 times.
at the end they simply gave it to him!

366
00:27:54.239 --> 00:27:56.119
Aaah... thanks for making me feel better...!

367
00:27:56.199 --> 00:27:57.199
You're welcome.

368
00:27:57.319 --> 00:28:01.119
Here. little David asked me
if you could fix that.

369
00:28:01.239 --> 00:28:02.959
Yeah. well. I'm not Super Mario!

370
00:28:03.079 --> 00:28:06.519
I know. you're Super Cop. you enforce the law...

371
00:28:06.554 --> 00:28:09.239
...and defend citizens against evil.

372
00:28:10.600 --> 00:28:14.920
Oh sweetie. you have a nice job.
I'm proud of you!

373
00:28:15.280 --> 00:28:18.240
Really!
Then why are you telling everybody I work for IBM?

374
00:28:18.320 --> 00:28:21.800
You want me to bring you
all the tickets from the neighborhood?

375
00:28:22.280 --> 00:28:22.640
No.

376
00:28:22.720 --> 00:28:26.200
Well then. you work for IBM
and they leave us alone.

377
00:28:27.280 --> 00:28:29.240
But I get to fix all the toys
from the neighborhood!

378
00:28:29.360 --> 00:28:30.600
You're miserable.

379
00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:32.240
Just kidding. mom!

380
00:28:33.280 --> 00:28:35.000
Can you call me a taxi? I'm running late.

381
00:28:35.120 --> 00:28:37.000
I just found a perfect one!

382
00:28:37.120 --> 00:28:41.120
Friendly. pleasant. the cream of the crop.
You'll love him!

383
00:28:43.280 --> 00:28:44.000
Hello?

384
00:28:44.280 --> 00:28:45.800
Am I on the wrong floor?

385
00:28:45.920 --> 00:28:47.280
It depends. who are you looking for?

386
00:28:47.360 --> 00:28:48.040
Camille.

387
00:28:48.120 --> 00:28:50.000
That's me. I mean. my mom.

388
00:28:50.121 --> 00:28:52.081
Oh you're the son... the one working for Apple?

389
00:28:52.121 --> 00:28:54.321
No. IBM. IBM! Mom!

390
00:28:55.241 --> 00:28:58.121
Well I don't know anything about those things.
I saw your picture the other day!

391
00:28:58.921 --> 00:29:01.801
Ah Daniel. that's my son Emilien.

392
00:29:01.921 --> 00:29:05.241
I've put labels on them...
Veal on Monday. on Tuesday...

393
00:29:05.321 --> 00:29:07.241
I'll be ok mom. I promise!

394
00:29:07.401 --> 00:29:10.281
We should get going. I left the car alone... Bye!

395
00:29:10.401 --> 00:29:11.721
Kiss!

396
00:29:11.761 --> 00:29:12.121
Kiss. mummy!

397
00:29:14.321 --> 00:29:15.041
Where are we going?

398
00:29:15.121 --> 00:29:16.121
Boulevard Voltaire.

399
00:29:16.321 --> 00:29:19.121
Hmmm... I remember the police station
but not IBM...

400
00:29:19.201 --> 00:29:20.281
Well that's where we're going.

401
00:29:21.321 --> 00:29:23.321
I'm installing computers there.

402
00:29:23.401 --> 00:29:27.721
You don't mind if I drop you off early?
I don't like hanging around them pigs.

403
00:29:34.362 --> 00:29:36.522
Tell me. that's a nice sound for a taxi!

404
00:29:36.602 --> 00:29:37.322
Oh. an expert!

405
00:29:38.202 --> 00:29:39.162
An amateur.

406
00:29:40.362 --> 00:29:45.122
It's a V6. a little bit modified.
You know. to make it sing a bit louder!

407
00:29:45.362 --> 00:29:48.922
Hey don't sing too loud.
the speed limit is 50!

408
00:29:49.002 --> 00:29:50.842
Ah. you're talking about the signs written "50"?

409
00:29:50.922 --> 00:29:51.722
Yep.

410
00:29:52.322 --> 00:29:54.202
I thought those applied to skateboards!

411
00:29:54.362 --> 00:29:56.322
Err... no. no.
I think it's for anything on wheels.

412
00:29:56.442 --> 00:29:59.322
Yeah but there is wheels and wheels!
You see I'm at 100...

413
00:29:59.442 --> 00:30:02.122
...a good car with a good driver.
there's no risk!

414
00:30:02.362 --> 00:30:05.122
I'm less dangerous at 100
then that piece of shit at 20 km/h...

415
00:30:05.202 --> 00:30:06.162
Watch this...

416
00:30:10.203 --> 00:30:11.203
Did you see that?

417
00:30:12.163 --> 00:30:13.163
You bet I've seen it!

418
00:30:14.403 --> 00:30:15.523
You're not afraid of radar traps?

419
00:30:15.603 --> 00:30:16.923
See. I know where they are.

420
00:30:17.403 --> 00:30:20.723
Pigs don't like changes.
they're always feeding at the same place.

421
00:30:20.923 --> 00:30:22.523
You'll see. there is one just a bit ahead.

422
00:30:22.723 --> 00:30:25.923
Watch this. they are just too stupid!

423
00:30:26.323 --> 00:30:29.123
Shoot! Shoot! Shoot! Shoot!

424
00:30:29.923 --> 00:30:33.123
You know it's not their fault.
they just follow orders.

425
00:30:33.323 --> 00:30:35.363
But nobody forced them to sign up!

426
00:30:35.483 --> 00:30:37.363
Well sometimes I wonder if they were forced...

427
00:30:37.483 --> 00:30:39.803
'cause you really gotta be
stupid to join the cops!

428
00:30:39.923 --> 00:30:40.363
Look....

429
00:30:40.483 --> 00:30:42.403
...I work with them often...
...because of the computers...

430
00:30:42.483 --> 00:30:45.163
You know. the idea I had about them was wrong.

431
00:30:45.243 --> 00:30:47.203
Yeah? So I guess they're even worse then?

432
00:30:47.923 --> 00:30:53.003
Err... no. they're better...
Not all the cops are assholes. you know...

433
00:30:53.124 --> 00:30:57.124
Oh I'm sure. there are also
alcoholics. crooks. idiots...

434
00:30:57.444 --> 00:30:59.404
Honestly. just between us...

435
00:30:59.484 --> 00:31:04.124
...do you know just ONE normal person
who would dream about joining the Pigs?

436
00:31:05.124 --> 00:31:06.124
And taxi drivers?

437
00:31:06.204 --> 00:31:06.924
What about them?

438
00:31:07.124 --> 00:31:09.404
Do you know anybody that
would want to become a taxi driver?

439
00:31:09.524 --> 00:31:11.724
Those bastards. who only pick you up
when they feel like it?

440
00:31:11.804 --> 00:31:15.324
Who scream at you when you're out
of change and can't leave a tip?

441
00:31:15.524 --> 00:31:19.724
Spend all day boozing in the bars.
bitching and moaning about everything...

442
00:31:19.804 --> 00:31:24.404
...they're in bed with the cops
to screw other people...

443
00:31:24.524 --> 00:31:28.324
...and when they're married to a landlord.
there's a disaster just waiting to happen!

444
00:31:28.485 --> 00:31:29.925
You're not married to a landlord?

445
00:31:30.325 --> 00:31:32.285
- No...
- Well that's reassuring!

446
00:31:34.485 --> 00:31:37.925
Ok so maybe there are a few drivers
that are rude to customers.

447
00:31:38.485 --> 00:31:39.405
But they're not all like that!

448
00:31:39.525 --> 00:31:42.125
See? With the police it's the same thing.

449
00:31:42.205 --> 00:31:45.445
They're not all drunk at 6AM.
eager to beat up an innocent black guy...

450
00:31:45.565 --> 00:31:49.525
Some of them do their jobs. sir.
Just like you... and like me.

451
00:31:49.725 --> 00:31:51.445
Maybe... Yeah. maybe.

452
00:31:51.565 --> 00:31:53.965
But the problem is that
I'm not a real taxi driver.

453
00:31:54.045 --> 00:31:58.125
So you're driving a cab just for fun?
What's your real job. then?

454
00:31:58.205 --> 00:31:58.925
Well. let me show you...

455
00:32:27.526 --> 00:32:30.126
Do you have a bag...
I'm gonna throw up!

456
00:32:30.526 --> 00:32:32.486
Don't worry. as long as we're moving.
nothing will come out.

457
00:32:43.526 --> 00:32:44.526
Oh shit!

458
00:32:46.526 --> 00:32:49.126
I'm sorry sir.
that's the first time this happens!

459
00:32:49.247 --> 00:32:53.727
Usually the client gets out.
walks a bit... and only then...

460
00:32:55.567 --> 00:32:56.927
I'm really sorry. sir!

461
00:32:57.007 --> 00:32:58.527
I have to tell you a secret.

462
00:33:00.527 --> 00:33:01.727
Me too. it's not my real job...

463
00:33:03.127 --> 00:33:04.327
Oh...?

464
00:33:05.567 --> 00:33:06.727
Oh. no...!

465
00:33:06.807 --> 00:33:09.127
Oh. yes...!

466
00:33:12.567 --> 00:33:13.927
Last name and first name?

467
00:33:14.047 --> 00:33:15.127
Morales. Daniel.

468
00:33:15.567 --> 00:33:18.527
Profession... should I write
"crazy taxi driver" or just "roadhog"?

469
00:33:19.567 --> 00:33:20.367
Do whatever you want.

470
00:33:20.927 --> 00:33:21.527
Ok...

471
00:33:22.527 --> 00:33:24.327
How fast were you going down the avenue?

472
00:33:24.527 --> 00:33:26.327
Oh. about 90...

473
00:33:26.567 --> 00:33:27.527
About 90?

474
00:33:27.727 --> 00:33:30.447
Well it seemed like more
because it's a good car...

475
00:33:30.528 --> 00:33:32.208
...but in fact. we were barely moving...

476
00:33:35.528 --> 00:33:37.608
- Hey. world champion. how's it going?
- Just great...

477
00:33:37.648 --> 00:33:39.928
Would you please go check out the
toilets to see if I'm there?

478
00:33:40.608 --> 00:33:43.328
Hey. remember the taxi?
We caught it again 5 minutes ago.

479
00:33:43.608 --> 00:33:46.528
Going 190 km/h. He's slowing down!

480
00:33:48.328 --> 00:33:52.528
You see? It wasn't 90... but 190!

481
00:33:54.608 --> 00:33:58.328
Ah... must've been the sun.
I didn't see the "1" on the tacho...

482
00:33:58.528 --> 00:34:03.328
That's why I was so relaxed!
If I had known. I would've slowed down!

483
00:34:03.608 --> 00:34:07.608
Well 90 is illegal anyway.
The limit is 50... for everybody!

484
00:34:07.688 --> 00:34:10.608
It applies to cars. skateboards. taxis...
EVERYBODY!

485
00:34:10.689 --> 00:34:14.609
Lil' cop happy now?
He got me. he did his job well. he's happy.

486
00:34:15.649 --> 00:34:20.129
Well my licence is my life.
If I lose my car tonight. I'll be dead tomorrow.

487
00:34:20.649 --> 00:34:24.129
So please. just cut the crap
and finish me off quickly. ok?

488
00:34:24.649 --> 00:34:27.609
Hey hey slow down.
I'm allowed to enjoy this a bit!

489
00:34:27.729 --> 00:34:31.329
Usually I'm the one who gets screamed at.
so now that for once I'm lucky...

490
00:34:31.649 --> 00:34:33.529
I didn't knock 'cause my wrist hurts.

491
00:34:33.609 --> 00:34:34.129
Oh. that doesn't matter...!

492
00:34:34.209 --> 00:34:36.129
That you didn't knock. I mean...

493
00:34:36.209 --> 00:34:36.729
Thanks...

494
00:34:36.849 --> 00:34:38.929
About your dinner.
your software that can't wait...

495
00:34:39.009 --> 00:34:39.329
Yes?

496
00:34:39.409 --> 00:34:41.409
Well it will have to wait
until my scars disappear!

497
00:34:41.489 --> 00:34:43.649
Unless you want to have dinner
with a scarecrow.

498
00:34:43.729 --> 00:34:46.649
But it doesn't bother me...
Err... I mean. you're perfect. Petra!

499
00:34:46.729 --> 00:34:49.649
I mean. it's not important...
...err I mean...

500
00:34:49.730 --> 00:34:54.410
Yes it is important.
I'm sorry. I feel bad for you...

501
00:34:54.490 --> 00:34:57.530
...and for me...
But that's ok...

502
00:35:00.850 --> 00:35:04.930
Ah you see!
It's like that all day!

503
00:35:05.690 --> 00:35:08.130
If only I could catch
those German bastards...

504
00:35:08.690 --> 00:35:10.930
Are you gonna finish me off?
You'll see. it'll make you feel better.

505
00:35:12.690 --> 00:35:17.130
Well yeah. I will have to...
...unless... you got an idea?

506
00:35:17.690 --> 00:35:19.330
I could promise not to do it again?

507
00:35:19.410 --> 00:35:20.930
I said an idea. not bullshit!

508
00:35:21.010 --> 00:35:24.330
I'm talking about a real idea...
of public interest!

509
00:35:24.690 --> 00:35:26.730
You want me to pick up doggy poop?

510
00:35:26.810 --> 00:35:27.930
Duh...!

511
00:35:28.731 --> 00:35:31.691
Something of public interest...for me.
You understand?

512
00:35:32.731 --> 00:35:36.451
Think that I am representing the public...

513
00:35:36.571 --> 00:35:40.931
... and you do something... for me! Got it now?

514
00:35:41.331 --> 00:35:42.531
Ah I see. you want money!

515
00:35:42.571 --> 00:35:43.811
Are you stupid or what?!

516
00:35:43.931 --> 00:35:47.931
Well then tell me clearly what you want
instead of babbling for an hour!

517
00:35:48.131 --> 00:35:49.331
What - do - you - want?

518
00:35:49.411 --> 00:35:49.931
Well ok.

519
00:35:50.731 --> 00:35:52.691
The "Mercedes gang"... does that ring a bell?

520
00:35:52.811 --> 00:35:54.691
The only gangs that I know ride choppers...

521
00:35:54.811 --> 00:35:57.691
Well that gang is in bankrobbery.
Yesterday was the 7th.

522
00:35:57.811 --> 00:35:59.131
It's driving my boss nuts.

523
00:35:59.211 --> 00:35:59.691
Ah. that sucks...

524
00:35:59.811 --> 00:36:03.531
Yes. mostly for us...
Listen. I'll offer you a deal.

525
00:36:04.251 --> 00:36:06.731
You're a car wizard and I need a good driver.

526
00:36:06.811 --> 00:36:11.531
So I'm hiring you as a trainee for 1 month.
Then I'll clear your file.

527
00:36:12.332 --> 00:36:14.452
You want me to play cop for 1 month?

528
00:36:14.612 --> 00:36:16.332
It's your choice. a cop or a pedestrian.

529
00:36:17.772 --> 00:36:20.452
I can choose Death or Shame?

530
00:36:20.532 --> 00:36:21.332
Exactly!

531
00:36:22.772 --> 00:36:26.532
Here you have all 7 attacks in order.

532
00:36:27.132 --> 00:36:29.812
You know. I'm no Mercedes specialist...
I'm more into Ferrari...

533
00:36:29.932 --> 00:36:33.532
Well right now the gang is "Mercedes"
but I'll tell you once they switch to Ferrari!

534
00:36:34.772 --> 00:36:36.532
Pfff... a red Mercedes. how ugly!

535
00:36:36.612 --> 00:36:39.932
I can see that it's red.
tell me something I don't know!

536
00:36:40.132 --> 00:36:42.732
We looked everywhere but you never know...

537
00:36:43.012 --> 00:36:44.532
...maybe a detail.

538
00:36:44.732 --> 00:36:45.932
Yeah. talk about a detail!

539
00:36:46.012 --> 00:36:46.532
What?

540
00:36:46.932 --> 00:36:50.332
Your gang. they are German?

541
00:36:50.813 --> 00:36:55.733
Ah nice! Mercedes = Germans!
Want a break? You must be exhausted now...!

542
00:36:55.893 --> 00:36:57.773
Their front tires are overinflated
which is typical of Germans.

543
00:36:57.853 --> 00:37:02.533
Their 8" tires were ordered from Germany
'cause you can't find those here.

544
00:37:02.613 --> 00:37:04.773
They look worn out. so they will
need to change them soon.

545
00:37:04.893 --> 00:37:07.773
On this picture. the muffler is a little bent
but not on this one.

546
00:37:07.893 --> 00:37:10.933
They must have bent it during an attack
and got it repaired after wards.

547
00:37:11.013 --> 00:37:13.333
Krueger is the only guy in Marseille
that can repair those.

548
00:37:13.413 --> 00:37:15.933
And Krueger... is German.

549
00:37:19.733 --> 00:37:21.933
Lucky you are not a Mercedes expert!

550
00:37:23.933 --> 00:37:24.933
Where are we going?

551
00:37:25.133 --> 00:37:27.733
To check out Krueger.
let's see what he remembers...

552
00:37:32.654 --> 00:37:35.534
Well what are you waiting for?
You want me to sing for you?

553
00:37:40.694 --> 00:37:42.934
If I were you. I'd take the garland off
in a neighborhood like this...

554
00:37:43.934 --> 00:37:45.334
What are we doing now?

555
00:37:45.414 --> 00:37:49.334
We begin the phase
that takes up 90% of a cop's life...

556
00:37:49.534 --> 00:37:51.134
... observation.

557
00:37:51.854 --> 00:37:55.334
We get acquainted with the area.
we survey the entries and exits...

558
00:37:55.414 --> 00:37:57.334
...and analyse the situation.

559
00:37:57.414 --> 00:38:00.334
And at closing time.
we'll go ask Mr. Krueger a few questions.

560
00:38:01.934 --> 00:38:03.734
What time does the garage close. please?

561
00:38:03.854 --> 00:38:06.134
Who. Krueger? He never closes. he's an insomniac!

562
00:38:06.334 --> 00:38:07.814
Aaah... thanks!

563
00:38:10.535 --> 00:38:12.135
They didn't have anything else.

564
00:38:12.695 --> 00:38:15.735
Too bad we didn't stop by at my mum's
she makes terrific sandwiches...

565
00:38:15.815 --> 00:38:20.535
MMMM her ham and cheese melt...
Half Bayonne and half Parisian ham...

566
00:38:20.895 --> 00:38:22.535
...it's simply wonderful.

567
00:38:22.615 --> 00:38:23.735
She made you one?

568
00:38:23.815 --> 00:38:24.535
Yeah...

569
00:38:24.895 --> 00:38:29.935
A small slice of Swiss cheese in the middle
with fresh lettuce leaves...

570
00:38:30.135 --> 00:38:34.335
...and with a few pickles...
Aaah. fantastic!

571
00:38:34.895 --> 00:38:35.735
But that's mine!

572
00:38:35.815 --> 00:38:38.335
Oh. really? Well it's awesome. congratulations!

573
00:38:50.336 --> 00:38:51.536
Now what's that guy doing?

574
00:38:51.616 --> 00:38:52.536
They are Koreans.

575
00:38:52.936 --> 00:38:56.536
They're a real pain in the ass for my job.
They work 24 hours a day.

576
00:38:56.616 --> 00:38:59.336
Well they gotta sleep at some point.
they're only human...

577
00:38:59.456 --> 00:39:00.736
No. you'll see. they got the knack.

578
00:39:01.336 --> 00:39:04.736
One taxi. one license. one permit....

579
00:39:06.336 --> 00:39:07.536
...but 2 drivers!

580
00:39:07.936 --> 00:39:10.336
I dare you to recognize
the difference between two Koreans!

581
00:39:11.736 --> 00:39:12.936
That's unbelievable!

582
00:39:18.936 --> 00:39:23.336
By the way I know a Korean...
He's in the cooking business. Wanna meet him?

583
00:39:23.416 --> 00:39:25.696
No. First we wait for that garage to close.

584
00:39:25.776 --> 00:39:28.536
We ain't there yet. the guy's
an insomniac. he never closes...

585
00:39:29.977 --> 00:39:31.537
How do you know that?

586
00:39:31.937 --> 00:39:33.817
I asked the bar owner next door.

587
00:39:34.337 --> 00:39:36.337
Then why didn't you tell me before?

588
00:39:36.977 --> 00:39:39.337
I'm a newbie. I don't have
those reflexes yet. chief...!

589
00:39:39.417 --> 00:39:42.537
But you don't have to be a cop for that.
it's just common sense. damned!

590
00:39:42.977 --> 00:39:45.937
We are here like 2 idiots
waiting for an insomniac to go to sleep!

591
00:39:46.217 --> 00:39:47.937
Does that sound logical to you?

592
00:39:49.977 --> 00:39:52.937
Now if I were the Mercedes driver
and knew my mechanic is an insomniac...

593
00:39:53.057 --> 00:39:55.737
...I'd come during the night.
It's more discreet. right?

594
00:39:55.817 --> 00:39:58.337
Oh yeah? You think that
the driver will pull up just like that...

595
00:39:58.537 --> 00:39:59.777
...in his brand-new Mercedes?

596
00:40:09.338 --> 00:40:10.338
I can't believe it!

597
00:40:10.818 --> 00:40:13.338
A driver. if he's not driving.
he'll be in a garage.

598
00:40:14.138 --> 00:40:15.338
What are they doing there?

599
00:40:15.538 --> 00:40:17.938
Probably getting those 8" tires from Krueger.

600
00:40:18.338 --> 00:40:21.618
That's a miracle!
I can't pass up such an opportunity.

601
00:40:22.018 --> 00:40:25.338
If there's a problem. call HQ
and give the license number. ok?

602
00:40:25.418 --> 00:40:26.138
Where are you going?

603
00:40:26.338 --> 00:40:27.738
After the Observation comes the Action.

604
00:40:28.138 --> 00:40:29.338
I'll do the Korean trick.

605
00:40:29.418 --> 00:40:29.978
What?

606
00:40:30.098 --> 00:40:31.138
The Korean trick!

607
00:40:37.338 --> 00:40:39.538
What a jerk!

608
00:40:39.738 --> 00:40:41.938
And where do you think they'll put the tires...?

609
00:40:45.018 --> 00:40:46.138
What are you doing there?

610
00:40:46.218 --> 00:40:47.938
Me? Err... sleeping?

611
00:40:48.339 --> 00:40:52.939
Me no house. country mine very cold...

612
00:40:53.139 --> 00:40:57.779
Noooo! Please!
No hurt me. me just sleeping!

613
00:40:57.899 --> 00:41:00.939
I'm going to find you a house
to sleep in...

614
00:41:01.139 --> 00:41:03.339
...and even eat if you're lucky!

615
00:41:22.739 --> 00:41:23.819
Hey. that hurts!

616
00:41:23.939 --> 00:41:25.139
I'm doing what I can!

617
00:41:30.100 --> 00:41:31.340
What's your name again?

618
00:41:31.420 --> 00:41:31.940
Daniel.

619
00:41:32.100 --> 00:41:35.060
Ah. yeah. Daniel.
I'm Emilien.

620
00:41:36.100 --> 00:41:38.540
Let's be pals. that'll make life easier...

621
00:41:38.740 --> 00:41:39.340
Yeah. right...

622
00:41:40.100 --> 00:41:44.060
So now that we are friends.
what just happened...

623
00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:47.140
...it stays between us. ok...?

624
00:41:47.540 --> 00:41:48.140
Ok...

625
00:41:49.340 --> 00:41:52.940
Do you think you could let go of my hand
so I can go get some sleep?

626
00:41:53.340 --> 00:41:56.140
I'm neither insomniac nor Korean...

627
00:41:56.940 --> 00:41:57.900
Sure...

628
00:42:02.340 --> 00:42:04.100
I waited for you all night.

629
00:42:04.180 --> 00:42:06.540
I did it on purpose so you'd really want me...

630
00:42:06.740 --> 00:42:08.540
You won't regret the waiting!

631
00:42:09.141 --> 00:42:13.341
Always promises... let's see facts for a change!

632
00:42:20.141 --> 00:42:23.341
Not bad... down a little bit further...

633
00:42:32.141 --> 00:42:34.101
What? What's going on?

634
00:42:34.341 --> 00:42:36.941
It's 6 AM and it's not Sunday but Monday!

635
00:42:37.981 --> 00:42:40.541
You can't do that Lily!
I waited all night.

636
00:42:40.741 --> 00:42:42.541
And what do you think I did?

637
00:42:42.621 --> 00:42:43.901
Can't you call in sick?

638
00:42:43.981 --> 00:42:46.901
Right. sick on a Monday...
My boss would love it...

639
00:42:46.981 --> 00:42:48.901
As if nobody pulled that one before.

640
00:42:48.982 --> 00:42:50.902
So? Anybody could get sick on a Monday morning!

641
00:42:50.982 --> 00:42:53.902
You went to eat at your parents
you ate too much...

642
00:42:53.982 --> 00:42:55.902
...and you puked all night.
Ain't that possible?

643
00:42:56.022 --> 00:43:01.142
And a man that works all week
but stays with his girlfriend on Sunday...

644
00:43:01.342 --> 00:43:02.342
...ain't that possible?

645
00:43:02.742 --> 00:43:06.342
I'm so sorry. Lily.
I really had a shitty day.

646
00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:11.342
But I promise that if you go out to with me
tonight. I'll explain everything.

647
00:43:12.542 --> 00:43:15.142
Ok. but I don't want to be sick Tuesday morning!

648
00:43:15.262 --> 00:43:17.742
Allright. a short time at the table
and a long time in bed.

649
00:43:18.542 --> 00:43:20.342
We could even eat in bed to save time!

650
00:43:21.182 --> 00:43:23.542
You'd better be good.
that's your last chance.

651
00:43:25.142 --> 00:43:26.142
I'm gonna rule!

652
00:43:30.743 --> 00:43:33.143
Are we going to wait again
all day in front of the garage?

653
00:43:33.343 --> 00:43:36.143
No. The Observation is done.
now comes the Questioning.

654
00:43:37.223 --> 00:43:39.743
Do you want to see how it's done?

655
00:43:40.223 --> 00:43:40.743
No...

656
00:43:40.823 --> 00:43:42.183
Well. you're coming anyway!

657
00:43:42.303 --> 00:43:46.183
But I'd be useless!
I'd rather watch the taxi in case there's trouble!

658
00:43:46.303 --> 00:43:49.543
I need a translator.
In case he gets too technical!

659
00:43:49.743 --> 00:43:52.543
Krueger won't have time to say a lot anyway.

660
00:43:58.743 --> 00:43:59.543
Good morning guys!

661
00:44:00.943 --> 00:44:03.543
Which one of you is Krueger. please?

662
00:44:03.743 --> 00:44:06.743
It's the same as for waiters.
It's written on the label.

663
00:44:06.943 --> 00:44:09.743
Mr Krueger.
I need to ask a few questions.

664
00:44:09.944 --> 00:44:11.744
Don't worry it won't be long...

665
00:44:37.264 --> 00:44:38.544
Fuck. I'm out of bullets!

666
00:44:38.624 --> 00:44:41.144
What for? They are long gone!

667
00:44:41.224 --> 00:44:43.744
- Really?
- Open you eyes. the garage is empty!

668
00:44:44.544 --> 00:44:45.744
Ah yeah. nobody there...!

669
00:44:46.544 --> 00:44:48.144
Ah yeah. nobody there...!

670
00:44:48.545 --> 00:44:50.545
Can I ask you a question?

671
00:44:50.745 --> 00:44:51.345
What?

672
00:44:51.545 --> 00:44:55.025
Do your questionings always
work like that or was that to please me?

673
00:44:55.145 --> 00:44:57.345
Well. usually I ask at least one question...!

674
00:44:57.745 --> 00:45:00.345
Come. let's go out and get some fresh air.

675
00:45:01.305 --> 00:45:02.345
You know. you saved my life there...

676
00:45:02.425 --> 00:45:03.745
- Bof...
- Yes you did.

677
00:45:04.305 --> 00:45:06.745
As a reward. you won't be cop for a month...

678
00:45:06.785 --> 00:45:07.225
Thanks!

679
00:45:07.305 --> 00:45:10.265
...it will only last a week.

680
00:45:10.385 --> 00:45:12.145
Thanks for nothing!

681
00:45:12.185 --> 00:45:14.145
Look. I really need to catch that gang.

682
00:45:14.345 --> 00:45:15.945
- Because of the blonde bimbo?
- No!

683
00:45:17.305 --> 00:45:19.945
No. Well. in part yes.
but it's mostly important for me.

684
00:45:19.985 --> 00:45:22.305
I'm tired of finishing every night in a trash can.

685
00:45:22.385 --> 00:45:25.745
It's a question of honor.
Sounds stupid. but I need this.

686
00:45:26.305 --> 00:45:27.945
Can I still have the night off?

687
00:45:28.066 --> 00:45:29.546
But of course...!

688
00:45:30.226 --> 00:45:31.746
Are you done. can I borrow him now?

689
00:45:31.786 --> 00:45:32.546
But Mom. you see...

690
00:45:32.626 --> 00:45:35.746
But I lost my prescription
and the doctor agreed to write another one.

691
00:45:35.826 --> 00:45:39.746
They are closing in 5 minutes.
It's my heart medication.

692
00:45:40.306 --> 00:45:44.506
I won't let you die here.
I'll have saved the whole family today!

693
00:45:44.586 --> 00:45:46.346
You're so charming. Daniel!

694
00:45:46.386 --> 00:45:47.146
I know. I know...

695
00:45:59.946 --> 00:46:02.146
Oh my God Johnny. here they come.

696
00:46:02.186 --> 00:46:02.946
Don't worry baby.

697
00:46:03.026 --> 00:46:06.346
I put a bug in that bullet.
they can't get away now.

698
00:46:06.546 --> 00:46:08.946
You're so clever. Johnny...

699
00:46:09.027 --> 00:46:10.147
It's my job. baby!

700
00:46:14.747 --> 00:46:17.347
Bullseye! You're so talented...

701
00:46:17.427 --> 00:46:19.347
Now all we gotta do is follow them...

702
00:46:19.387 --> 00:46:22.347
- That's amazing!
- ...let's go save your father.

703
00:46:22.747 --> 00:46:25.147
I'll never forget
what you've done for me. Johnny...

704
00:46:25.227 --> 00:46:26.147
It's my job. baby!

705
00:46:34.427 --> 00:46:37.747
Ok guys. we just received a call there.

706
00:46:38.427 --> 00:46:41.147
So now. they're even getting a date with us!

707
00:46:41.427 --> 00:46:43.747
It will be the Marseille Bank.

708
00:46:44.427 --> 00:46:47.387
Since they are so precise with us
I'm going to be the same with you.

709
00:46:47.508 --> 00:46:50.748
I won't tolerate ANY misbehavior or accident!
Nothing!

710
00:46:50.788 --> 00:46:52.948
I want perfect coordination!

711
00:46:53.428 --> 00:46:55.428
Two words to this mission:

712
00:46:55.748 --> 00:46:56.948
Serenity...

713
00:46:58.468 --> 00:46:59.548
...and efficiency.

714
00:47:01.468 --> 00:47:03.428
That's why I decided
to call this mission...

715
00:47:04.468 --> 00:47:05.428
The mission...

716
00:47:07.468 --> 00:47:08.428
...Zen.

717
00:47:11.468 --> 00:47:12.148
Chief!

718
00:47:12.548 --> 00:47:15.948
Let go of the grass snakes and cobras.
I just got the idea of the century!

719
00:47:16.028 --> 00:47:20.548
The mercedes gang will be nailed tonight
or I'm not Emilien Barbadec.

720
00:47:27.349 --> 00:47:29.749
"The best chicken in Marseille"

721
00:47:29.949 --> 00:47:33.149
I hope you plan is fool proof Emilien
'cause this is your last bullet.

722
00:47:35.509 --> 00:47:39.749
You're the one with that bullet
so do me a favor... don't miss!

723
00:47:43.509 --> 00:47:45.469
Everybody on the floor!
Quick!

724
00:47:45.549 --> 00:47:48.469
Hands up!

725
00:47:49.509 --> 00:47:51.469
Lie down! Don't move!

726
00:47:51.589 --> 00:47:53.269
Come on!

727
00:48:11.670 --> 00:48:12.350
It's working!

728
00:48:12.550 --> 00:48:15.150
Oh yeah? That's good. very good.

729
00:48:33.390 --> 00:48:34.950
Follow them at a distance.

730
00:48:45.150 --> 00:48:46.550
That way you won't be scared!

731
00:49:03.151 --> 00:49:06.511
They stopped. Gauguin Street.
I told you. we got them!

732
00:49:07.591 --> 00:49:09.551
Gilbert here.

733
00:49:09.671 --> 00:49:13.551
All units: block all traffic on 10km
around Gauguin Street.

734
00:49:27.552 --> 00:49:30.552
They still didn't move.
Just one street more.

735
00:49:38.432 --> 00:49:39.432
What happened?

736
00:49:39.672 --> 00:49:42.152
I... The dot vanished!

737
00:49:42.232 --> 00:49:43.592
I can see that!

738
00:49:43.672 --> 00:49:45.952
I wanna know why it vanished!

739
00:49:46.072 --> 00:49:47.552
Slow down. they must be close by!

740
00:49:47.672 --> 00:49:49.352
...a red Mercedes shouldn't be hard to find!

741
00:50:04.632 --> 00:50:06.432
The're close. I can feel it.

742
00:50:08.633 --> 00:50:09.753
They should be right here.

743
00:50:13.553 --> 00:50:14.953
Hold it right there!

744
00:50:17.673 --> 00:50:19.633
Go. go. go!

745
00:50:21.673 --> 00:50:24.153
Don't shoot!
I'm just the hostage!

746
00:50:28.513 --> 00:50:29.473
Emilien...

747
00:50:30.673 --> 00:50:31.473
But how...?

748
00:50:33.673 --> 00:50:36.153
I don't get it.
I'm missing something here.

749
00:50:36.233 --> 00:50:39.153
How can a red Mercedes vanish?
Even Copperfield never managed that!

750
00:50:43.753 --> 00:50:45.953
Hello.
Your papers please.

751
00:50:47.674 --> 00:50:49.274
What is happening. sir?

752
00:50:49.674 --> 00:50:50.754
You're German?

753
00:50:50.834 --> 00:50:51.554
Yes. why?

754
00:50:51.674 --> 00:50:52.954
Are we already at the border?

755
00:50:54.554 --> 00:50:57.874
Chief. 4 Germans in a not red Mercedes.
You're interested?

756
00:50:57.914 --> 00:50:58.274
I'm taking it.

757
00:51:00.714 --> 00:51:02.154
So you're German?

758
00:51:02.234 --> 00:51:03.954
You got a problem with that?

759
00:51:04.034 --> 00:51:06.674
Today I like that actually.
Open the trunk.

760
00:51:07.714 --> 00:51:09.354
What did you come to Marseille for?

761
00:51:09.434 --> 00:51:10.754
I came to spend my Deutschmark....

762
00:51:10.794 --> 00:51:13.154
...but I can do that
in another country if you prefer!

763
00:51:13.234 --> 00:51:13.994
Oh no....

764
00:51:14.034 --> 00:51:16.554
...I prefer you keep that
in our territory!

765
00:51:23.754 --> 00:51:26.354
Ok... auf Wiedersehen. have a nice stay.

766
00:51:26.474 --> 00:51:27.554
Danke sch?n!

767
00:51:30.955 --> 00:51:32.155
Emilien...

768
00:51:32.555 --> 00:51:35.555
I don't get it. I just don't get it.
I must have forgotten something...

769
00:51:35.755 --> 00:51:39.755
You see. he forgot the kettle. Classic.

770
00:51:39.835 --> 00:51:42.155
You think? But he's not like that...

771
00:51:44.555 --> 00:51:49.555
It's 8 PM. I've put the answering machine
and the alarm at 6 AM.

772
00:51:49.755 --> 00:51:51.555
We've got 10 hours. That should be enough. no?

773
00:51:51.635 --> 00:51:53.555
It's a little bit tight...

774
00:51:53.595 --> 00:51:55.955
...we'll just have to hurry towards the end!

775
00:52:01.755 --> 00:52:02.555
Are you expecting somebody?

776
00:52:03.155 --> 00:52:06.155
Well. my lover. but when you said
that you'd come. I cancelled...

777
00:52:08.956 --> 00:52:10.156
Who could it be?

778
00:52:10.556 --> 00:52:12.956
Don't mind him. he'll leave...

779
00:52:13.356 --> 00:52:13.956
Where were we?

780
00:52:14.756 --> 00:52:17.436
Err... I was kissing you.

781
00:52:17.596 --> 00:52:19.356
No. you were kissing me!

782
00:52:24.356 --> 00:52:25.756
What if it was important?

783
00:52:25.956 --> 00:52:26.556
Why?

784
00:52:26.796 --> 00:52:28.756
I don't know... the cops...

785
00:52:28.876 --> 00:52:31.756
Ah yes. if you were a notorious criminal
and they come to get you.

786
00:52:31.876 --> 00:52:36.156
You would take me hostage...
Just take me now...

787
00:52:37.796 --> 00:52:39.356
Open. police!

788
00:52:39.436 --> 00:52:41.156
Daniel. you didn't kill anybody I hope!

789
00:52:42.636 --> 00:52:43.596
Err... no.

790
00:52:44.796 --> 00:52:46.756
Oh shit. Daniel!

791
00:52:47.557 --> 00:52:48.557
Am I glad you're here!

792
00:52:49.357 --> 00:52:50.957
You can't imagine the shit I'm in Daniel.

793
00:52:51.157 --> 00:52:51.957
Oh yes I can imagine...

794
00:52:51.997 --> 00:52:54.557
No. no you can't imagine.

795
00:52:54.837 --> 00:52:56.797
It's over. we don't have a home.

796
00:52:56.877 --> 00:52:59.357
We lost the flat my father gave us.

797
00:52:59.837 --> 00:53:01.557
Gone in smoke. just like my father.

798
00:53:01.757 --> 00:53:03.357
My husband smoked a lot...

799
00:53:03.437 --> 00:53:06.557
...yet he died of liver cancer.
even though he didn't drink...

800
00:53:07.837 --> 00:53:10.797
In fact it's not about the flat.
Much worse is that I screwed up again.

801
00:53:10.917 --> 00:53:14.557
If I don't catch them this week.
I'll be a traffic cop next Monday!

802
00:53:14.837 --> 00:53:17.557
Stick. wistle. go ahead kids!

803
00:53:17.837 --> 00:53:20.157
It's as to say. on Monday... I'm dead.

804
00:53:21.837 --> 00:53:23.557
Daniel. who's that dwarf?

805
00:53:23.637 --> 00:53:24.237
A pal.

806
00:53:24.357 --> 00:53:26.597
You're playing with Smurfs now?

807
00:53:26.678 --> 00:53:28.158
It's a bit complicated. he's a cop...

808
00:53:28.238 --> 00:53:28.958
What?

809
00:53:29.038 --> 00:53:30.558
You've got a friend in the police?

810
00:53:30.638 --> 00:53:31.038
Not a real friend...

811
00:53:31.158 --> 00:53:32.358
...I work for him. because...

812
00:53:32.438 --> 00:53:33.358
You work for the cops?

813
00:53:33.438 --> 00:53:36.838
Not for the cops. for HIM!
He's not really a cop...

814
00:53:36.918 --> 00:53:40.838
...he looks more like a secret agent.
something like that.

815
00:53:40.918 --> 00:53:43.558
Yeah sure. and the old lady is Mata Hari.

816
00:53:43.878 --> 00:53:47.758
Oh shit... can anybody explain her?
Because I don't think I can.

817
00:53:47.878 --> 00:53:49.838
My name is Camille. hello...

818
00:53:49.958 --> 00:53:52.838
... and the Smurf over there
is my son. Emilien.

819
00:53:52.958 --> 00:53:55.758
And if you show me to the kitchen.

820
00:53:55.838 --> 00:53:57.958
I'll make you a good coffee
and I'll explain everything.

821
00:53:58.158 --> 00:53:58.918
There's nothing to explain. mom...

822
00:53:58.958 --> 00:54:03.958
...I'm done. I'm in the street...
It had started so well. though...

823
00:54:04.758 --> 00:54:08.958
...but then came the garbage cans.
the butchers. the Mercedes...

824
00:54:08.999 --> 00:54:12.559
So? Are you gonna kick your homeless friends out
or should I call the REAL cops?

825
00:54:12.639 --> 00:54:15.079
Hey stop it. don't make the situation worse. ok?

826
00:54:15.159 --> 00:54:16.639
I'm not complicating the situation.

827
00:54:16.719 --> 00:54:19.924
I just want to finish what we had started.

828
00:54:19.959 --> 00:54:23.559
And I don't want to waste an hour
because we are very tight on schedule!

829
00:54:23.639 --> 00:54:26.959
Look. I got caught in the harbour...
...I mean. seriously caught.

830
00:54:27.039 --> 00:54:28.879
They could keep my license for the next 100 years.

831
00:54:28.999 --> 00:54:33.559
But if help him. I'll get it back.
It's that or 100 years of unemployment!

832
00:54:34.159 --> 00:54:35.959
Cop. Blackmailer. Smurf...

833
00:54:35.999 --> 00:54:38.959
Nice portrait. you could have finished it
before setting him loose!

834
00:54:39.039 --> 00:54:42.359
Here you go. that was completely stupid of me.

835
00:54:45.359 --> 00:54:48.959
I'm not kidding Daniel....you're free.

836
00:54:49.920 --> 00:54:50.560
Take it.

837
00:54:54.960 --> 00:54:58.560
You know. Daniel.
I didn't come here because of our deal.

838
00:54:58.960 --> 00:55:02.760
It's just that I ain't got any other friends...
and Mom told me you had a big heart.

839
00:55:06.360 --> 00:55:09.760
"Daniel has a big heart. right?
See. he'll help us?"

840
00:55:15.960 --> 00:55:18.760
Ok I think we were wrong... it doesn't matter.

841
00:55:19.960 --> 00:55:23.960
It's not important. it's not your problem.

842
00:55:24.960 --> 00:55:28.360
Don't you worry. Daniel.
I'll catch that gang alone.

843
00:55:30.961 --> 00:55:35.161
Won't be easy without a driver... but I'll manage.

844
00:55:42.001 --> 00:55:45.161
Listen. the best way to get rid of him
is to solve his problem.

845
00:55:45.361 --> 00:55:49.561
But he doesn't have A problem.
he's got TONS! He's a psycho!

846
00:55:49.761 --> 00:55:52.961
Look at his face.
it reminds me of "Silence of the Lambs".

847
00:55:53.161 --> 00:55:55.881
You take care of Mata Hari
and me of the Smurf.

848
00:55:55.961 --> 00:55:57.681
I'm back in 2 hours.

849
00:55:57.761 --> 00:55:59.561
And what am I gonna do with grandma for 2 hours?

850
00:55:59.961 --> 00:56:00.961
Play bingo?

851
00:56:01.161 --> 00:56:03.361
Please. Lily. ok?

852
00:56:03.561 --> 00:56:05.961
If you're not back in 2 hours. I'll BURN grandma.

853
00:56:06.001 --> 00:56:06.761
Deal!

854
00:56:08.002 --> 00:56:08.962
Get up. you.

855
00:56:09.042 --> 00:56:10.562
- Where are we going?
- To solve your problem.

856
00:56:13.842 --> 00:56:16.002
I'm sorry to have ruined your evening.

857
00:56:17.682 --> 00:56:19.762
You really make a good coffee?

858
00:56:20.162 --> 00:56:21.562
The best in town!

859
00:56:34.162 --> 00:56:37.362
A small coffee to change the mood
and to say I'm sorry.

860
00:56:42.162 --> 00:56:46.762
I know you don't really want to talk to me anymore
But listen up please.

861
00:56:46.843 --> 00:56:47.563
Ok?

862
00:56:47.643 --> 00:56:48.963
You got 1 minute.

863
00:56:49.043 --> 00:56:53.803
It'll do. Ok. I thought about it all night
and there was a question I couldn't answer.

864
00:56:53.843 --> 00:56:55.803
Why are they pissing us off like that?

865
00:56:55.883 --> 00:56:58.763
Why a red Mercedes
when grey is much more discrete?

866
00:56:58.963 --> 00:57:02.763
To get our attention!
We look here. and then!

867
00:57:02.883 --> 00:57:06.803
...it happens there.
It's a diversion.

868
00:57:06.923 --> 00:57:12.083
So I think they left the building empty handed
and the money took another way out.

869
00:57:12.163 --> 00:57:14.763
Maybe the money is even still in the bank.

870
00:57:18.243 --> 00:57:20.963
1 minute. end of the show.

871
00:57:27.364 --> 00:57:28.964
I'll be back!

872
00:58:00.244 --> 00:58:01.284
10 grand.

873
00:58:01.364 --> 00:58:02.644
Thank you very much.

874
00:58:02.764 --> 00:58:04.964
That'll pay your rent for a while.

875
00:58:05.564 --> 00:58:06.764
And my wife?

876
00:58:07.965 --> 00:58:09.765
You really want her back?

877
00:58:11.165 --> 00:58:13.165
Well. I kinda got used to her...

878
00:58:18.965 --> 00:58:21.125
Calm down. dear!

879
00:58:21.365 --> 00:58:25.965
Look... everything's going to be fine now.

880
00:58:33.165 --> 00:58:36.565
Gentlemen. one more and we retire...

881
00:58:37.485 --> 00:58:43.365
And for the last one. I suggest we hit it big.

882
00:58:50.166 --> 00:58:52.966
Emilien. Emilien!

883
00:58:53.166 --> 00:58:54.086
Piss off!

884
00:58:54.166 --> 00:58:57.926
What if I told you how they changed
from a red to a grey mercedes?

885
00:58:58.006 --> 00:58:59.766
Sure. go ahead...

886
00:58:59.846 --> 00:59:02.766
They didn't change the car.
they just changed the color.

887
00:59:03.206 --> 00:59:06.766
A nice. red Mercedes enters a parking...

888
00:59:07.166 --> 00:59:10.566
...and a classic grey mercedes
exits and dissappears.

889
00:59:10.646 --> 00:59:11.766
That sounds possible.

890
00:59:11.846 --> 00:59:12.926
Easy as pie.

891
00:59:13.046 --> 00:59:16.966
If they did repaint the car
we would have found paint traces somewhere.

892
00:59:17.046 --> 00:59:20.766
Except if they put their car in a truck
and repainted it in there.

893
00:59:21.206 --> 00:59:24.166
They need tons of paint
if they do that every time!

894
00:59:24.246 --> 00:59:29.966
Plus. they had less than 10 minutes!
Can you even get paint that dries in 10 min?

895
00:59:30.047 --> 00:59:32.967
Hello. G�g�?
Sorry for waking you up. it's Daniel.

896
00:59:33.767 --> 00:59:36.167
I need your magic paint. the LT10.

897
00:59:36.967 --> 00:59:38.367
Metal grey color.

898
00:59:39.567 --> 00:59:44.567
You're out of it?
Who could have bought all that in one shot?

899
00:59:45.167 --> 00:59:46.967
The "circuit des �tangs"?

900
00:59:47.367 --> 00:59:50.967
What are they doing with that much paint
they want to paint the circuit in red?

901
00:59:51.767 --> 00:59:54.967
No. thanks. don't worry
I'll talk to them directly.

902
00:59:55.367 --> 00:59:57.567
Talk to you soon. thanks man.

903
00:59:59.767 --> 01:00:01.567
What does "LT10" mean?

904
01:00:01.647 --> 01:00:02.967
"Less Than 10 minutes".

905
01:00:16.088 --> 01:00:17.768
So? You like my theory?

906
01:00:23.568 --> 01:00:24.768
You think it's them?

907
01:00:24.848 --> 01:00:28.168
No. stupid. it's the butcher
team's regular training...!

908
01:00:29.288 --> 01:00:31.968
Hey. tell me Daniel. What's the plan. now?

909
01:00:32.368 --> 01:00:33.848
What are you doing?

910
01:00:33.968 --> 01:00:34.928
We are going to say hi!

911
01:00:34.968 --> 01:00:36.168
Are you crazy. they'll see us!

912
01:00:36.208 --> 01:00:37.648
They're not gonna forget us. either!

913
01:00:37.728 --> 01:00:41.288
But they'll recognize me Daniel.
they saw me well in the trunk!

914
01:00:41.368 --> 01:00:42.168
Put that on.

915
01:00:42.248 --> 01:00:42.968
Ah shit!

916
01:00:45.128 --> 01:00:46.088
Is that ok?

917
01:00:47.289 --> 01:00:48.969
You're perfect!

918
01:00:51.169 --> 01:00:55.169
Hey faggots. is everything ok?
Think you are Schumacher?

919
01:00:55.569 --> 01:00:58.769
Happy spinning around in circles?
Let me see your little toys there...

920
01:00:59.369 --> 01:01:00.569
Oh. Mercedes?

921
01:01:01.329 --> 01:01:05.049
Oh dear... they build cars too?
Do you Germans know "turtle and hare"?

922
01:01:05.169 --> 01:01:07.369
You don't know that game?
I'm gonna show you.

923
01:01:07.449 --> 01:01:08.289
Give me 55.

924
01:01:10.169 --> 01:01:11.769
Maybe I should get out now. no?

925
01:01:11.849 --> 01:01:13.969
Don't worry. I'm sure they're playful.

926
01:01:14.329 --> 01:01:16.769
"Turtle and hare" goes like this:

927
01:01:17.329 --> 01:01:20.969
You win 55 if you pass my car within 2 laps.
That's 1 + 1.

928
01:01:21.049 --> 01:01:22.169
You know how to count?

929
01:01:22.249 --> 01:01:23.249
We don't want the money.

930
01:01:23.369 --> 01:01:26.169
I said 55 because I don't want
to steal more from you.

931
01:01:26.330 --> 01:01:29.570
But a tourist that doesn't get screwed
is not really a tourist. no?

932
01:01:29.690 --> 01:01:33.090
Hey. if I'm already behind you
again after the first lap....

933
01:01:33.170 --> 01:01:36.650
...don't drive the second lap
for nothing. honey!

934
01:01:48.570 --> 01:01:49.370
Thanks girls!

935
01:01:52.370 --> 01:01:55.170
Get lost!
Quick!

936
01:01:55.370 --> 01:01:59.370
It's not that I'm bored
but I gotta go to the garage.

937
01:01:59.450 --> 01:02:02.170
I don't know what's wrong.
but my car is a bit slow today...

938
01:02:03.970 --> 01:02:06.370
We'll do the rematch whenever you want...

939
01:02:11.211 --> 01:02:11.971
Here are your 55.

940
01:02:12.051 --> 01:02:13.371
What are we doing now?

941
01:02:13.451 --> 01:02:14.171
Let's get a drink.

942
01:02:18.211 --> 01:02:19.771
Frenchies...

943
01:02:20.491 --> 01:02:23.171
Are you completely crazy?
We had the gang and you just goof off!

944
01:02:23.251 --> 01:02:25.371
We could have called backups and jailed them!

945
01:02:25.771 --> 01:02:27.571
Oh yeah. for what motive?

946
01:02:27.771 --> 01:02:29.171
For speeding on a circuit?

947
01:02:29.251 --> 01:02:30.451
Pfff. the evidence...

948
01:02:30.571 --> 01:02:32.451
We'd have found it later.
as usual...

949
01:02:32.571 --> 01:02:35.971
Hold it. Do we have to catch them in the act?
Yes or no?

950
01:02:36.011 --> 01:02:38.211
Well maybe. but right now WE are getting trouble.

951
01:02:38.331 --> 01:02:41.771
If we continue like this. WE will get jailed!

952
01:02:41.971 --> 01:02:45.451
Ok. ok. listen. We'll get them in the act.

953
01:02:46.532 --> 01:02:50.172
They are raging now
and nobody's more playful than a driver.

954
01:02:50.252 --> 01:02:52.892
Now we can build them a nice little trap.

955
01:02:52.972 --> 01:02:54.772
Yeah? What kind of trap?

956
01:02:54.852 --> 01:02:56.172
A trap for idiots.

957
01:02:56.372 --> 01:02:57.972
And what's your "idiot trap"?

958
01:02:58.052 --> 01:02:59.312
Not an "idiot trap"!

959
01:02:59.347 --> 01:03:00.572
A trap FOR idiots.

960
01:03:00.652 --> 01:03:02.172
Ok. So how does it work?

961
01:03:02.252 --> 01:03:06.572
It works like this.
We bring them to wherever we want.

962
01:03:06.652 --> 01:03:08.772
And that's right... here!

963
01:03:09.532 --> 01:03:12.532
I'll need 20 red light keys
and 20 talkies.

964
01:03:16.572 --> 01:03:20.372
Ok for the talkies but I don't have a key
and the guys always watch theirs.

965
01:03:20.972 --> 01:03:22.172
Except when they take their shower.

966
01:03:25.772 --> 01:03:27.172
- Oh... no!
- Oh... yes!

967
01:03:27.373 --> 01:03:28.373
- Oh no!
- Oh yes!

968
01:03:28.573 --> 01:03:29.573
- Oh no!
- Oh yes!

969
01:03:55.573 --> 01:03:56.773
You're a natural!

970
01:03:57.613 --> 01:03:58.653
Here you go. Jimmy.

971
01:04:05.613 --> 01:04:07.373
Hurry up. I'm freezing my ass off here!

972
01:04:07.454 --> 01:04:07.974
One minute.

973
01:04:08.614 --> 01:04:09.574
Emilien. I...

974
01:04:10.614 --> 01:04:12.174
What are you doing in your birth suit?

975
01:04:15.374 --> 01:04:19.374
I'm not naked.
I'm wearing a towel. ok!

976
01:04:19.974 --> 01:04:22.174
And what's it to you anyway?

977
01:04:22.614 --> 01:04:24.574
I got the right to be naked in my office. no?

978
01:04:24.694 --> 01:04:25.774
It's MY office. no?

979
01:04:25.974 --> 01:04:26.614
Well yes...

980
01:04:26.694 --> 01:04:29.494
Nobody ever taught you to knock before entering?

981
01:04:29.574 --> 01:04:32.374
